In Two Pointer Technique, we typically use two index variables from two corners of an array.
We use the two pointer technique for searching a required point or value in an array.

Two pointers is really an easy and effective technique that is typically used for Two Sum in Sorted Arrays,
Closest Two Sum, Three Sum, Four Sum, Trapping Rain Water and many other popular interview questions.
Given a sorted array arr (sorted in ascending order) and a target, find if there exists any pair of elements (arr[i], arr[j]) such that their sum is equal to the target.

